She said they were carrying on a sexual relationship and discussed several plans to kill Lisa Knoefel, including shooting her and making it look like a burglary, or finding a hit man. 

Zunich testified that she put on a ski mask and fatally stabbed 41-year-old Lisa Knoefel in her bed as she fought back in November 2012, when she was 17.

Prosecutors said Zunich stabbed and cut her more than 150 times with a 10-inch serrated knife.

She was not deterred even though Knoefel fought and pleaded for her to stop and the woman's teenage daughter tried to pull Zunich off her mother and called 911.

Prosecutors have said they were unaware of Zunich's sexual relationship with Kevin Knoefel or that he had persuaded her to kill Lisa Knoefel until Zunich spoke with them in May, 2013. 

